Fresh Pi session: MAKE THE CURRENT AND ALL PREVIOUS TESTS PASS.

Inputs:
- Selected scenario: latest {{run.dir}}/tdd/current-scenario-*.json
- Deterministic red execution and semantic assessment: latest red verification/report under {{run.dir}}/tdd/
- Repository constraints: {{run.dir}}/design/repository-constraints.md
- Prior issues: {{run.issues-file}}
- Worktree: {{run.worktree-dir}}

Goal:
Change production code only as needed to make the new test and all previous tests pass.

Rules:
- Do not delete, skip, or weaken assertions and do not rewrite expected values from observed output without independent justification.
- Keep red-to-green separate from refactoring; make the smallest clear behavior change.
- Run the focused test and relevant prior tests while implementing when useful. The next process node independently executes the latest focused manifest for every scenario.
- If implementation reveals another behavioral case, record it in the discoveries JSON instead of implementing or testing it now.
- Always write discoveries JSON; use an empty `scenarios` array when none were found.
- Do not push or create a PR.
- Commit the coherent green increment locally when tests pass.

Write:
- Summary: {{run.dir}}/tdd/green-summary-{{run.round}}.md
- Discoveries: {{run.dir}}/tdd/discovered-scenarios-{{run.round}}.json
- Status: {{run.dir}}/tdd/green-status-{{run.round}}.json
- On failure: {{run.dir}}/tdd/green-issues-{{run.round}}.json

Discovery shape:
{"scenarios":[{"description":"...","expected_behavior":"...","source":"discovered-while-making-green"}]}

Status examples:
{"status":"pass","summary":"current and previous tests pass","issues_file":null}
{"status":"fail","summary":"green work remains","issues_file":"tdd/green-issues-{{run.round}}.json"}
